{"title":"New Giro Supernatural gloves are a chamois for your hands, Trixter MTB gloves bring the value","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/23/giro-eit-team-up-on-chamois-for-your-palm-trixter-mtb-gloves-offer-impressive-value/","date":1614106060000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>For many riders, wearing cycling shorts with an integrated chamois is just part of riding a bike. That’s allowed companies like Elastic Interface to become experts in chamois technology and comfort, which is exactly why Giro has worked with EIT on their shorts for years. But now, the two companies have developed a new Elastic Interface – one meant for your palms instead of your rear.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" alt=\"Giro &amp; EIT palm chamois pressure testing\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb8/ng:webp/ngcb8\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 630w\" ezoid=\"0.23585774407147442\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RD-test_6-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 630w\"></a></p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8yzLVQf7plQ?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\"></iframe></span></p><p>Co-developed for Giro’s cycling gloves, the EIT Palm Technology can be found on the new Supernatural road gloves. Calling it the “first ever three-dimensional seamless and elastic palm” for cycling gloves, the EIT Palm was developed in conjunction with the University of Padua Department of Biomedical Sciences. More than just slapping some new materials into a stretchy palm, pressure sensors were used in the development process to help determine the best locations for specific padding.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand.jpg\" alt=\"Giro &amp; EIT palm chamois options\" width=\"1018\" height=\"886\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1018px) 100vw, 1018px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand.jpg 1018w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-297x258.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-800x696.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-120x104.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-768x668.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-696x606.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-483x420.jpg 483w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand.jpg 1018w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-297x258.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-800x696.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-120x104.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-768x668.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-696x606.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-EIT-Palm-technology-chamois-for-your-hand-483x420.jpg 483w\"></a></p><p>Like chamois for your shorts, there are different models of the EIT Palm including Race, Gravel, Ultra, and Slim models using various densities of their Hybrid Cell System inserts. Those inserts are 3-D molded in to a seamless, one piece palm and positioned to improve blood flow and reduce pressure on the ulnar nerve. And since the palm is elastic, it will stretch and move with your hand, conforming to your grip on the bars or hoods.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface.jpg\" alt=\"Giro &amp; EIT palm technology for Supernatural glove\" width=\"1200\" height=\"798\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-632x420.jpg 632w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Palm-by-Elastic-Interface-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/w