-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-2-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The fourchettes (the area between the fingers) is construction from AX Bolt fabric with InstaChill technology that has a cooling effect once it becomes moist. Between that, and the airy construction, I probably won’t be using these gloves any time soon – but they seem like a great option for the hotter months.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><p>The Trixter is unisex with a simple slip-on elastic cuff, and comes in five colors for $20.</p><h2>Havoc</h2><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-8.jpg\" alt=\"Giro Havoc MTB glove \" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-8.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-