or-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-7-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-7-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-7-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-7-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-7-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Giro-Trixter-and-Havoc-mountain-bike-gloves-one-piece-AX-suede-microfiber-palm-MTB-7-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>This time, a true AX Suede one-piece, pre-curved microfiber palm is used with perforations and conductive stitching for smartphone use. Compared to the Microfiber palm used for the Trixter, the AX Suede palm has a softer feel to it, but both offer excellent feedback from the bar.</p><p>Offered in four colors, the Havoc sells for $40.</p><h2>Fit</h2><p>I tend to run between a small and a medium in terms of glove sizing, and I’d say that both of these gloves run true to size or slightly smaller. Because of that, the Havoc is easier for me to get over my wide palms – though both fit pretty well once I’ve got them on. I prefer my gloves snug without any bunching of material or loose bits a the end of the fingers and initially these seem to fit pretty well.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.giro.com/c/mens-bike-gloves\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>giro.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d3d701dc51ae44662d45664894a65a57de3dbc44e38bac495bcd4356d209d4b1","category":"Cycling"}